1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Lymph nodes are immune checkpoints where cells meet antigens.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:08,400
These tiny structures might seem small, but they’re essential in our defense.

3
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:12,800
When pathogens invade, lymph nodes spring into action, gathering immune cells.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:17,200
Research shows they can influence how effectively our immune system responds.

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:22,400
So, next time you feel under the weather, remember the unseen battle within.

